    "tagline": "Odysseus came home to quiet water",
    "summary": "Ithaca is the island Odysseus spent ten years trying to reach, and the surprise is how little it asks of you once you arrive. It sits just across the strait from Kefalonia — a short ferry hop from Sami or Agia Efimia — yet it feels a step further out of reach, greener and slower, its harbours folded deep into the hills. Vathy wraps around one of the most sheltered bays in the Ionian, a working town of faded neoclassical houses and a waterfront that empties out by mid-afternoon.\n\nWhat stays with you is the stillness of the coves. The water in the small inlets is the kind of clear that makes the boats look like they are floating on air. Kioni and Frikes, on the green north end, are little more than a curve of tavernas and bobbing masts. It is an island for a slow day — a swim, a long lunch by the water, the ferry back as the light softens.",
