    "tagline": "Our gateway to the Ionian.",
    "summary": "Patras is less a destination than a hinge — Greece's third city, built at the foot of Mount Panachaikon and looking out over its own gulf toward the islands. For us it is mostly a port: the place where the mainland hands us over to Kefalonia, or takes us back. The ferries to Sami leave from the north (old) port, and the ticket office is at Gate 2.\n\nStill, if there is time before boarding, the upper town rewards a short wander. The Roman-era castle sits above the harbour with wide views over the water, and the neoclassical Apollon Theatre — a small mirror of La Scala, built by Ernst Ziller in 1872 — anchors the squares below. It is a working city, not a polished one: arcaded streets, students, café tables, the smell of diesel and sea. We pass through rather than linger, and that feels right.",
