    "summary": "Below the village of Planitero, the Aroanios river simply begins — karst water seeping up through sandy gravel across a narrow strip of ground, a hundred tiny outflows gathering into a real brook within a few steps. The whole thing happens under a forest of centuries-old plane trees, some with trunks close to four meters across, so the light comes through green and the air stays cool even when the lowlands are baking.\n\nThis is a place to do almost nothing. You walk the short shaded paths along the channels, watch the old stone watermill still turning on the current, and then sit at one of the tavernas built right over the water. The draw is trout, raised in the spring-fed farms beside you and grilled simply — order it, take your time, listen to the water. It is exactly the kind of slow, green, low-key stop the rest of the day can be built around.",
