    "tagline": "Three and a half hours across the Ionian",
    "summary": "This is the seam of the trip — the slow afternoon crossing that carries us and the car from the mainland onto Kefalonia, and a week later carries us back. Levante Ferries runs the Patras–Sami line, and we are on the F/B Andreas Kalvos: out at 13:00 on 22 Aug, arriving Sami at 16:30, and the early return at 08:30 on 29 Aug. Three and a half hours of open Ionian water, lounge seats booked, the car waiting below.\n\nIt does not feel like transit so much as a deliberate pause. Patras falls away, the Peloponnesian coast softens, and there is nothing to do but watch the light move on the sea. By mid-afternoon the green ridges of Kefalonia rise ahead and Sami's small harbour opens up. The return is quieter still — leaving at first light, coffee in hand, the island receding while the day is barely awake.",
